           SPELL=gbuffy
         VERSION=0.2.4
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.fiction.net/blong/programs/gbuffy/$SOURCE
   SOURCE_URL[1]=ftp://download.sourcemage.org/pub/linux/distributions/sourcemage/mirror/$SOURCE
     SOURCE_HASH=sha512:2e220754e9b425e5382402728c28fbc9655dc0ae901b8a7b8e4362a05db1946c07e290b6c75b55e50ebf3b6119d7464e6c395d05cd845d0fd5e25a840fe59c17
        WEB_SITE=http://www.fiction.net/blong/programs/gbuffy
         ENTERED=20020131
         UPDATED=20020131
      MAINTAINER=jbooks@roundthestarts.net
      LICENSE[0]=http://www.fiction.net/blong/programs/gbuffy
        KEYWORDS="mail"
           SHORT="GBuffy is a GTK+ multiple mailbox "biff" program."
    MENU_ITEM[0]=${SPELL}
    MENU_EXEC[0]=${SPELL}
    MENU_DESC[0]=${SHORT}
cat << EOF
GBuffy will poll multiple mailboxes for new mail. It will list the
number of new messages in each mailbox you configure. It will also
highlight the mailboxes that have new mail, and you can display the
message headers by pressing mouse button one on a mailbox. GBuffy is
currently capable of watching MBOX, MMDF, Maildir and MH Folders.
This version also supports IMAP4rev1 and NNTP with XOVER mailboxes,
as well as displaying X-Face headers.
EOF
